references.reason: This paper is foundational to the concept of adversarial examples, which are central to the proposed ADV-TRA fingerprinting method.

references.paper_title: IPGuard: Protecting intellectual property of deep neural networks via fingerprinting the classification boundary
references.reason: This paper introduces a significant prior fingerprinting method (IPGuard) which ADV-TRA improves upon.

references.paper_title: Deep neural network fingerprinting by conferrable adversarial examples
references.reason: This paper is a key reference for existing model fingerprinting techniques, providing a baseline for comparison with ADV-TRA.

references.paper_title: Fingerprinting deep neural networks globally via universal adversarial perturbations
references.reason: This paper proposes another important model fingerprinting technique (UAP) that uses universal adversarial perturbations, offering a different approach than ADV-TRA.

references.paper_title: Copy, right? A testing framework for copyright protection of deep learning models
references.reason: This paper introduces a comprehensive framework for evaluating model fingerprinting methods, relevant to the evaluation done in the current paper.
